Here's how to implement all three in your `EditProductPage`:

**1 & 2. Intercept back navigation with a confirmation dialog**

Override `OnBackButtonPressed` and use the `Shell.Current.Navigation` API:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Fire-and-forget; return true to cancel the hardware/back gesture
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () =>
            {
                bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                    "Unsaved Changes",
                    "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                    "Discard", "Stay");

                if (leave)
                    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
            });

            return true; // cancel the default back navigation
        }

        return base.OnBackButtonPressed(); // allow normal navigation
    }
}
```

> `OnBackButtonPressed` handles the **hardware/gesture** back button (Android back, swipe). Return `true` to cancel it.

**3. Custom "Cancel" back button in the toolbar**

Replace Shell's default back button with your own `ToolbarItem` or `BackButtonBehavior`:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Title="Edit Product">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior
            TextOverride="Cancel"
            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}"
            IconOverride="" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

Then in your view model (or code-behind):

```csharp
public ICommand CancelCommand { get; }

public EditProductViewModel()
{
    CancelCommand = new Command(async () =>
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave) return;
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    });
}
```

**Key points:**
- `OnBackButtonPressed` → handles system/gesture back
- `Shell.BackButtonBehavior` → handles the **Shell navbar** back button (text, icon, command)
- You need **both** to fully guard against unsaved-change loss
- `GoToAsync("..")` navigates back one page in Shell's URI scheme
